  "texts": [
    "Moreover, many forms of tremendously important influences, such as testimony or influences that 'activate heuristics', bypass rationality but are not examples of manipulation.",
    "Hence, the bypassing criterion is also over-inclusive and generative false positives.",
    "For example, testimony bypasses rationality because it is often accepted at face value, given a positive evaluation of the source's credibility.",
    "This is not a rational process in the sense of being conscious, yet testimony is unlikely to be a form of manipulation.",
    "Similarly, the availability or recognition heuristic allows people to make frugal decisions without conscious deliberation."
  ],
